<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Dikmer on 04-07-2001 05:54 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">My last post for awhile, but I just wanted to throw this in.

I know I have bad luck. I know if it weren't for the generosity of friends, I would asve nothing. I know if it weren't for NBG I would have nothing.

Case in point:

Was in Hate last night, and the cleric drops were as so...
8 clerics, 1 already in FULL EM, one with a BP, 2 with legs.

Arms drop, 2 people roll, one winds (Fuggo)
Legs drop, 4 clerics roll (Fuggo was out due to winning arms), Yumien wins.
Arms drop again, no one rolls (I have donals and didn't need EM Arms), Yumien loots to prevent rotting.
Legs and shield drop on same cleric. 3 clerics roll on legs, I lost.
Legs drop AGAIN (3rd pair). Now only TWO clerics in zone eligible to roll. And guess what? Connection servers crashed. We worked it out afterwards, and I WOULD have won. By the time people were able to get back in, they had rotted. 

If it were not for good luck, I would have no luck at all.

So, I am STILL after the ever ellusive 200wis. 190wis, and no hope of getting higher for a long while.

This is why I support NBG. I know I never win anything on a random. I know that even should I win something on a random, something happens that makes me wish I had never won in the first place. I am going to abstain myself from ever rolling on anything again, and if someone hands me something, great and if not, I'll just go on with what I have. At least now, what I have is mine and not borrowed. </TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
